# Lattice Project Rules

## Architecture

- **Backend**: Flask (Python) in `backend/`, SQLite via Flask-SQLAlchemy, Flask-Login sessions
- **Frontend**: React + Vite in `frontend/`, Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/vite`), Lucide icons
- API proxy: Vite proxies `/api` to `http://localhost:5001`

## Backend Conventions

- All routes live in Flask blueprints under `backend/app/` (auth.py, documents.py, canvas.py)
- Every database query must be scoped to `current_user.id` to enforce per-user isolation
- Return JSON responses with appropriate HTTP status codes (201 for create, 200 for read/update, 404 for not found)
- Use `werkzeug.security` for password hashing, never store plaintext passwords
- File uploads go to `backend/uploads/`, thumbnails to `backend/thumbnails/`

## Frontend Conventions

- Components in `frontend/src/components/`, pages in `frontend/src/pages/`
- Use functional components with hooks, no class components
- Auth state managed via `AuthContext`; use `useAuth()` hook
- API calls go through the shared Axios instance at `frontend/src/api/axios.js`
- Tailwind utility classes only -- no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Use `lucide-react` for all icons

## Canvas Interactions

- Document nodes are absolutely positioned inside a relative canvas container
- Drag via native pointer events (onPointerDown/Move/Up), no external DnD library
- Connections rendered as SVG `<line>` elements in an overlay that matches canvas dimensions
- Persist positions to backend on pointer up; optimistic local updates during drag

## Running the App

- Backend: `cd backend && source venv/bin/activate && python run.py` (port 5001)
- Frontend: `cd frontend && npm run dev` (port 5173, proxies /api to backend)
